<br>
It's just insane how usefull it is.  Just last night I was grouped with a wizzie and we were solo pulling Bandits in FG using CoTH.  He would root one, then train away the other 3.  I would run over and annul the rooted one, bring him to camp and when he was on Pet, I would CoTH the wizzie back.  Every once in awhile we got adds, or I was too low to COTH, so he would run the others by and I would keep them rooted while we finished them off one at a time.<br>
<br>
The root lasts for like 96 seconds, 4 sec cast.  So you can root NPC's as they are running strait for you as long as they are not SoW speed.  It does not overwrite lvl 57 earth root though, so If I'm going to use earring for all my roots when soloing I use a different pet.<br>
<br>
I can TOTALLY deal with adds now, and I have saved my groups tons of times now by rooting running mobs.  Never need a spell slot, fast cast, and no mana.  It's just insane.  The stats are nice too.  Not to mention, when dueling people and not using earth, they are a little suprised when they suddenly get rooted.  It's soooo good for that too.  Root somebody, back out to BOLT range and cast.  When root breaks, start clicking earring until it starts casting.  It will land way before they get in range and cast a spell.  Then I just back up out of their range again and BOLT again.  It's pretty damn hard for people to do anything about that.<br>
<br>
